The paper deals with value function approximation and policy iteration in Markov decision processes (MDPs) with a factorized structure, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of dynamic Bayesian networks and variable elimination algorithms also suggests a connection to probabilistic graphical models and inference (cs.DM). The focus on system dynamics and policy manipulation suggests a connection to control theory and systems engineering (cs.SY), while the use of optimization techniques suggests a connection to robotics (cs.RO).
